      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Tough, honest driver with good bones and plenty of usable life left. The powertrain pulls through the rev range, transmission engages as it should, and the chassis still feels planted enough to make this a solid commuter, weekend beater, or starter project. Cosmetic wear and age-related imperfections are present, but the car remains straightforward to own, easy to wrench on, and affordable to get into. If you want dependable transportation with mechanical character and room to improve over time, this is a smart buy.",
